entries.name: CoinIssuer
entries.description: Manages the inflation and minting schedule of the Aztec token. It enforces an annual percentage cap and mints new tokens for the budget.

entries.name: StakingRegistry
entries.description: Manages staking providers for delegation.

entries.name: GovernanceProposer
entries.description: Intermediary contract that allows the L2 system (or specific L2 signals) to submit formal proposals to the L1 Governance contract.

entries.name: BaseStaker
entries.description: A template contract used for staker proxies within the StakingRegistry.

entries.name: Governance
entries.description: DAO contract used for proposals and token voting. Heavily interdependent with the GSE for voting power snapshots.

entries.name: Inbox
entries.description: Handles L1-to-L2 messaging. Users deposit funds or send messages here, which are organized into a Merkle tree for the sequencer to include in an L2 block.

entries.name: Registry
entries.description: Central directory that tracks the current 'canonical' (active) Rollup contract address and key system contracts like the Reward Distributor.

entries.name: RewardDistributor
entries.description: Holds tokens allocated for protocol rewards. The canonical Rollup contract calls this to distribute payments to sequencers and provers.

entries.name: Rollup
entries.description: Core rollup logic contract. It processes block proposals, verifies ZK proofs for state transitions, manages data availability, and coordinates validator selection and chain tip updates.

getManaLimit.description: gas limit, currently 0 to prevent transactions

entries.name: ProtocolTreasury
entries.description: Holds the protocol's funds controlled by Governance. It acts as a timelocked executor for spending or relaying transactions approved by the DAO.

entries.name: RewardBooster
entries.description: Calculates 'boosted' reward shares for active provers based on a configured curve, incentivizing consistent participation.

entries.name: HonkVerifier
entries.description: ZK proof verification contract.

entries.name: TallySlashingProposer
entries.description: Allows the validator committee to vote on slashing a specific peer. Once a quorum is reached, it proposes a slash action to the Slasher.

entries.name: ATPWithdrawableAndClaimableStaker
entries.description: Standard escrow implementation used to simplify and manage staking with locked AZTEC tokens.

entries.name: SlashPayloadCloneable
entries.description: A template for specific slashing payload contracts deployed deterministically to encode a slashing action (who to slash and how much) that the Slasher executes.

entries.name: AztecTokenPositionRegistry_Sequencers
entries.description: A registry for contracts related to Sequencer staking and token unlock parameters.

entries.name: Slasher
entries.description: The executor contract for penalties. It receives authorization to slash validator stakes, subject to an execution delay and a vetoer.

receivedPermissions.description: set the time at which the ProtocolTreasury funds can be transfered and manage staker implementations referenced by this contract.

entries.name: Aztec
entries.description: AZTEC token contract

entries.name: GSE
entries.description: Central staking manager independent of Rollup implementations. Sequencers deposit stake here through their chosen Rollup contract. Their stake is then transfered to the Governance contract and activated for voting. The GSE tracks which rollup instance validators are securing, and gives them an option to automatically move to the latest Rollup version.

entries.name: AztecTokenPositionRegistry_ProtocolTreasury
entries.description: Used to set the time at which AZTEC tokens owned by the ProtocolTreasury are unlocked.

entries.name: FeeJuicePortal
entries.description: A one-way public bridge to deposit AZTEC tokens to the Rollup.

entries.name: Outbox
entries.description: Handles L2-to-L1 messaging. It stores Merkle roots of messages exiting the rollup, allowing users to prove inclusion and finalize withdrawals or actions on L1.
